
Overview of verb widen

The verb widen has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (7) widen -- (become broader or wider or more extensive; "The road widened")
2. (1) let out, widen -- (make (clothes) larger; "Let out that dress--I gained a lot of weight")
3. (1) widen -- (make wider; "widen the road")
4. widen, broaden, extend -- (extend in scope or range or area; "The law was extended to all citizens"; "widen the range of applications"; "broaden your horizon"; "Extend your backyard")
